\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 College students have a set academic schedule and once extra circulars and homework are added to their workload, there is very little time left for social events. I tend to be in the habit of waking up, going to class, eating lunch, going back to class, eating dinner, homework, club meetings, bedtime almost every single day during the week. Although routines are a good way to ensure stability and time management, there comes to a point where the days morph together and every day feels the exact same. This can cause people to slip into a depressive state and impact the mental health of many students.
