\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 The most tedious part of this project was finding all of the sound clips and importing them into audacity. Since they are all separate tracks I had to make sure they lined up and scroll through them all when something needed to be changed. With this approach there were not many technical edits that needed to be made besides continually cutting the audio files for each \'93cycle\'94 and adjusting the audio to make sure one wasn\'92t outstandly loud compared to the others. I also have no experiences with anything digital media related so there was a large learning curve that needed to take place for me to be able to complete this assignment. A lot of my time was spent looking up how to complete certain tasks and edits on audacity. This assignment helped to expand some of my general knowledge on audio recordings and editing.\'a0 
